<section id="covenant" class="section">
    <div class="py-4 px-2 px-sm-4">
        <div class="section-heading mb-4">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-between section-toggle"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#covenantCollapse" role="button" 
                aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="covenantCollapse">
                <h2 class="display-6 w-100 d-flex m-0">
                    Covenant glyphs
                </h2>
                <span class="text-light px-1 border rounded align-self-end toggle-button">
                    <i class="bi bi-arrow-up lh-base"></i>
                </span>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <p class="px-2">
                Convert Covenant glyphs from the video game <a href="https://www.halowaypoint.com/" title="HaloWaypoint.com - the official site for the Halo universe" class="text-convrtr">Halo</a> to their text alternative, these glyphs were featured during an episode of the Halo 5: Guardians behdind the scenes show "<a href="https://www.halopedia.org/File:H5G_The_Sprint_Covenant_Font.png" title="Halopedia - Covenant Font image" class="text-convrtr">The Sprint</a>". The "Create image" button downloads an image version of the glyphs selected and displayed below the text version.
            </p>
            <p class="px-2">
                 There is more information available on the <a href="https://www.halopedia.org/Sangheili_(language)" class="text-convrtr">Sangheili language</a> Halopedia page. 
            </p>
        </div>
